{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"If we look around us,"},{"time":3000,"text":"much of what surrounds us"},{"time":5000,"text":"started life as various rocks and sludge"},{"time":8000,"text":"buried in the ground in various places in the world."},{"time":12000,"text":"But, of course, they don't look like rocks and sludge now."},{"time":14000,"text":"They look like TV cameras, monitors,"},{"time":17000,"text":"annoying radio mics."},{"time":19000,"text":"And so this magical transformation"},{"time":21000,"text":"is what I was trying to get at with my project,"},{"time":24000,"text":"which became known as the Toaster Project."},{"time":26000,"text":"And it was also inspired by this quote"},{"time":28000,"text":"from Douglas Adams,"},{"time":30000,"text":"and the situation is from \"The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy.\""},{"time":33000,"text":"And the situation it describes"},{"time":35000,"text":"is the hero of the book -- he's a 20th-century man --"},{"time":38000,"text":"finds himself alone on a strange planet"},{"time":41000,"text":"populated only by a technologically primitive people."},{"time":44000,"text":"And he kind of assumes that, yes,"},{"time":46000,"text":"he'll become -- these villagers --"},{"time":48000,"text":"he'll become their emperor"},{"time":50000,"text":"and transform their society"},{"time":52000,"text":"with his wonderful command of technology"},{"time":54000,"text":"and science and the elements,"},{"time":56000,"text":"but, of course, realizes"},{"time":58000,"text":"that without the rest of human society,"},{"time":60000,"text":"he can barely make a sandwich,"},{"time":63000,"text":"let alone a toaster."},{"time":65000,"text":"But he didn't have Wikipedia."}]},{"cues":[{"time":67000,"text":"So I thought, okay,"},{"time":69000,"text":"I'll try and make an electric toaster from scratch."},{"time":71000,"text":"And, working on the idea"},{"time":73000,"text":"that the cheapest electric toaster"},{"time":75000,"text":"would also be the simplest to reverse-engineer,"},{"time":77000,"text":"I went and bought the cheapest toaster I could find,"},{"time":80000,"text":"took it home"},{"time":82000,"text":"and was kind of dismayed to discover"},{"time":84000,"text":"that, inside this object,"},{"time":86000,"text":"which I'd bought for just 3.49 pounds,"},{"time":89000,"text":"there were 400 different bits"},{"time":92000,"text":"made out of a hundred-plus different materials."},{"time":96000,"text":"I didn't have the rest of my life to do this project."},{"time":99000,"text":"I had maybe nine months."},{"time":101000,"text":"So I thought, okay, I'll start with five."},{"time":103000,"text":"And these were steel, mica,"},{"time":105000,"text":"plastic, copper and nickel."}]},{"cues":[{"time":108000,"text":"So, starting with steel: how do you make steel?"},{"time":111000,"text":"I went and knocked on the door"},{"time":113000,"text":"of the Rio Tinto Chair"},{"time":115000,"text":"of Advanced Mineral Extraction at the Royal School of Mines"},{"time":118000,"text":"and said, \"How do you make steel?\""},{"time":120000,"text":"And Professor Cilliers was very kind"},{"time":122000,"text":"and talked me through it."},{"time":124000,"text":"And my vague rememberings from GCSE science --"},{"time":127000,"text":"well, steel comes from iron,"},{"time":129000,"text":"so I phoned up an iron mine."},{"time":132000,"text":"And said, \"Hi, I'm trying to make a toaster."},{"time":134000,"text":"Can I come up and get some iron?\""},{"time":138000,"text":"Unfortunately, when I got there -- emerges Ray."},{"time":141000,"text":"He had misheard me"},{"time":143000,"text":"and thought I was coming up because I was trying to make a poster,"},{"time":146000,"text":"and so wasn't prepared to take me into the mines."},{"time":149000,"text":"But after some nagging, I got him to do that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":151000,"text":"(Video) Ray: It was Crease Limestone,"},{"time":155000,"text":"and that was produced"},{"time":157000,"text":"by sea creatures"},{"time":160000,"text":"350 million years ago"},{"time":163000,"text":"in a nice, warm,"},{"time":165000,"text":"sunny atmosphere."},{"time":167000,"text":"When you study geology,"},{"time":169000,"text":"you can see what's happened in the past,"},{"time":172000,"text":"and there were terrific changes in the earth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":181000,"text":"Thomas Thwaites: As you can see, they had the Christmas decorations up."},{"time":185000,"text":"And of course, it wasn't actually a working mine anymore,"},{"time":188000,"text":"because, though Ray was a miner there,"},{"time":191000,"text":"the mine had closed"},{"time":193000,"text":"and had been reopened as a kind of tourist attraction,"},{"time":196000,"text":"because, of course, it can't compete"},{"time":198000,"text":"on the scale of operations which are happening"},{"time":201000,"text":"in South America, Australia, wherever."},{"time":204000,"text":"But anyway, I got my suitcase of iron ore"},{"time":207000,"text":"and dragged it back to London on the train,"},{"time":209000,"text":"and then was faced with the problem:"},{"time":211000,"text":"Okay, how do you make this rock"},{"time":213000,"text":"into components for a toaster?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":215000,"text":"So I went back to Professor Cilliers,"},{"time":217000,"text":"and he said, \"Go to the library.\""},{"time":219000,"text":"So I did"},{"time":221000,"text":"and was looking through the undergraduate textbooks on metallurgy --"},{"time":224000,"text":"completely useless for what I was trying to do."},{"time":227000,"text":"Because, of course, they don't actually tell you how to do it"},{"time":230000,"text":"if you want to do it yourself and you don't have a smelting plant."},{"time":233000,"text":"So I ended up going to the History of Science Library"},{"time":235000,"text":"and looking at this book."},{"time":237000,"text":"This is the first textbook on metallurgy"},{"time":239000,"text":"written in the West, at least."},{"time":241000,"text":"And there you can see that woodcut"},{"time":243000,"text":"is basically what I ended up doing."},{"time":245000,"text":"But instead of a bellows, I had a leaf blower."},{"time":248000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":250000,"text":"And that was something that reoccurred throughout the project,"},{"time":253000,"text":"was, the smaller the scale you want to work on,"},{"time":255000,"text":"the further back in time you have to go."},{"time":258000,"text":"And so this is after"},{"time":260000,"text":"a day and about half a night"},{"time":262000,"text":"smelting this iron."},{"time":264000,"text":"I dragged out this stuff,"},{"time":266000,"text":"and it wasn't iron."},{"time":268000,"text":"But luckily,"},{"time":270000,"text":"I found a patent online"},{"time":272000,"text":"for industrial furnaces that use microwaves,"},{"time":275000,"text":"and at 30 minutes at full power,"},{"time":277000,"text":"and I was able to finish off the process."}]},{"cues":[{"time":282000,"text":"So, my next --"},{"time":284000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":288000,"text":"The next thing I was trying to get was copper."},{"time":291000,"text":"Again, this mine"},{"time":294000,"text":"was once the largest copper mine in the world."},{"time":296000,"text":"It's not anymore,"},{"time":298000,"text":"but I found a retired geology professor"},{"time":300000,"text":"to take me down,"},{"time":302000,"text":"and he said, \"Okay, I'll let you have some water from the mine.\""},{"time":305000,"text":"And the reason I was interested in getting water"},{"time":308000,"text":"is because water which goes through mines"},{"time":310000,"text":"becomes kind of acidic"},{"time":312000,"text":"and will start picking up,"},{"time":314000,"text":"dissolving the minerals from the mine."},{"time":316000,"text":"And a good example of this is the Rio Tinto,"},{"time":319000,"text":"which is in Portugal."},{"time":321000,"text":"As you can see, it's got lots and lots of minerals dissolved in it."},{"time":324000,"text":"So many such"},{"time":326000,"text":"that it's now just a home for bacteria"},{"time":329000,"text":"who really like acidic, toxic conditions."},{"time":332000,"text":"But anyway, the water I dragged back"},{"time":334000,"text":"from the Isle of Anglesey where the mine was --"},{"time":336000,"text":"there was enough copper in it"},{"time":338000,"text":"such that I could cast the pins"},{"time":340000,"text":"of my metal electric plug."}]},{"cues":[{"time":342000,"text":"So my next thing: I was off to Scotland"},{"time":345000,"text":"to get mica."},{"time":348000,"text":"And mica is a mineral"},{"time":351000,"text":"which is a very good insulator"},{"time":354000,"text":"and very good at insulating electricity."},{"time":357000,"text":"That's me getting mica."},{"time":360000,"text":"And the last material I'm going to talk about today is plastic,"},{"time":363000,"text":"and, of course,"},{"time":365000,"text":"my toaster had to have a plastic case."},{"time":367000,"text":"Plastic is the defining feature"},{"time":369000,"text":"of cheap electrical goods."},{"time":371000,"text":"And so plastic comes from oil, so I phoned up BP"},{"time":374000,"text":"and spent a good half an hour"},{"time":376000,"text":"trying to convince the PR office at BP"},{"time":378000,"text":"that it would be fantastic for them"},{"time":380000,"text":"if they flew me to an oil rig"},{"time":382000,"text":"and let me have a jug of oil."},{"time":384000,"text":"BP obviously has a bit more on their mind now."},{"time":388000,"text":"But even then"},{"time":390000,"text":"they weren't convinced"},{"time":392000,"text":"and said, \"Okay, we'll phone you back\" -- never did."},{"time":395000,"text":"So I looked at other ways of making plastic."},{"time":398000,"text":"And you can actually make plastic"},{"time":400000,"text":"from obviously oils which come from plants, but also from starches."},{"time":403000,"text":"So this is attempting to make"},{"time":405000,"text":"potato starch plastic."},{"time":407000,"text":"And for a while that was looking really good."},{"time":409000,"text":"I poured it into the mold, which you can see there,"},{"time":411000,"text":"which I've made from a tree trunk."},{"time":413000,"text":"And it was looking good for a while,"},{"time":415000,"text":"but I left it outside, because you had to leave it outside to dry,"},{"time":418000,"text":"and unfortunately I came back"},{"time":420000,"text":"and there were snails eating the unhydrolyzed bits of potato."}]},{"cues":[{"time":424000,"text":"So kind of out of desperation,"},{"time":427000,"text":"I decided that I could think laterally."},{"time":430000,"text":"And geologists have actually christened --"},{"time":432000,"text":"well, they're debating whether to christen --"},{"time":434000,"text":"the age that we're living in --"},{"time":436000,"text":"they're debating whether to make it a new geological epoch"},{"time":439000,"text":"called the Anthropocene, the age of Man."},{"time":442000,"text":"And that's because geologists of the future"},{"time":444000,"text":"would kind of see a sharp shift"},{"time":446000,"text":"in the strata of rock that is being laid down now."},{"time":448000,"text":"So suddenly, it will become kind of radioactive from Chernobyl"},{"time":451000,"text":"and the 2,000 or so nuclear bombs"},{"time":453000,"text":"that have been set off since 1945."},{"time":457000,"text":"And there'd also be an extinction event --"},{"time":460000,"text":"like fossils would suddenly disappear."},{"time":463000,"text":"And also, I thought"},{"time":465000,"text":"that there would be"},{"time":467000,"text":"synthetic polymers,"},{"time":469000,"text":"plastics, embedded in the rock."}]},{"cues":[{"time":471000,"text":"So I looked up a plastic --"},{"time":473000,"text":"so I decided that I could mine"},{"time":475000,"text":"some of this modern-day rock."},{"time":477000,"text":"And I went up to Manchester"},{"time":479000,"text":"to visit a place called Axion Recycling."},{"time":482000,"text":"And they're at the sharp end of what's called the WEEE,"},{"time":485000,"text":"which is this European electrical and electronic waste directive."},{"time":490000,"text":"And that was brought into force"},{"time":492000,"text":"to try and deal with the mountain of stuff"},{"time":495000,"text":"that is just being made"},{"time":498000,"text":"and then living for a while in our homes"},{"time":500000,"text":"and then going to landfill."},{"time":502000,"text":"But this is it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":511000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":572000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":574000,"text":"So there's a picture"},{"time":576000,"text":"of my toaster."},{"time":578000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":582000,"text":"That's it without the case on."},{"time":585000,"text":"And there it is on the shelves."},{"time":588000,"text":"Thanks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":590000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":594000,"text":"Bruno Giussani: I'm told you did plug it in once."}]},{"cues":[{"time":596000,"text":"TT: Yeah, I did plug it in."},{"time":598000,"text":"I don't know if you could see,"},{"time":600000,"text":"but I was never able to make insulation for the wires."},{"time":603000,"text":"Kew Gardens were insistent"},{"time":605000,"text":"that I couldn't come and hack into their rubber tree."},{"time":608000,"text":"So the wires were uninsulated."},{"time":610000,"text":"So there was 240 volts"},{"time":612000,"text":"going through these homemade copper wires,"},{"time":614000,"text":"homemade plug."},{"time":616000,"text":"And for about five seconds,"},{"time":618000,"text":"the toaster toasted,"},{"time":620000,"text":"but then, unfortunately,"},{"time":622000,"text":"the element kind of melted itself."},{"time":625000,"text":"But I considered it a partial success, to be honest."}]},{"cues":[{"time":628000,"text":"BG: Thomas Thwaites. TT: Thanks."}]}]}